6	# Kit-Contributed Rig Templates, Writ Types, and Mappings
7	
8	## Summary
9	
10	Kits and apparatus supportKits can contribute writ types, rig templates, and writ-type-to-template mappings so that installing a plugin is sufficient to make a new work type functional. The Spider and Clerk consume these contributions at startup, merging them with guild config which retains override authority.
11	
12	## Current State
13	
14	### Spider (`packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.ts`)
15	
16	The Spider manages rig execution. At startup it reads `SpiderConfig` from `guild().guildConfig().spider`:
17	
18	```typescript
19	// packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts
20	export interface SpiderConfig {
21	  pollIntervalMs?: number;
22	  buildCommand?: string;
23	  testCommand?: string;
24	  rigTemplates?: Record<string, RigTemplate>;
25	  variables?: Record<string, unknown>;
26	}
27	```
28	
29	`rigTemplates` keys currently serve as both template names and writ-type-to-template mappings. `lookupTemplate()` does a direct property lookup:
30	
31	```typescript
32	function lookupTemplate(writType: string, config: SpiderConfig): RigTemplate {
33	  const templates = config.rigTemplates;
34	  if (templates) {
35	    if (writType in templates) return templates[writType];
36	    if ('default' in templates) return templates['default'];
37	  }
38	  throw new Error(
39	    `[spider] No rig template found for writ type "${writType}" and no "default" template configured.`
40	  );
41	}
42	```
43	
44	Called from `trySpawn()` at line 737:
45	
46	```typescript
47	const template = lookupTemplate(writ.type, spiderConfig);
48	```
49	
50	The Spider validates config templates at startup via `validateTemplates()` — checking non-empty engines, duplicate IDs, unknown designIds (against Fabricator + builtins), upstream refs, cycles, resolutionEngine, and variable refs. All errors throw.
51	
52	The Spider declares `consumes: ['blockTypes']` and scans kits using Phase 1 (`g.kits()`) + Phase 2 (`ctx.on('plugin:initialized', ...)`) via a `BlockTypeRegistry` class.
53	
54	The Spider's apparatus declaration:
55	
56	```typescript
57	apparatus: {
58	  requires: ['stacks', 'clerk', 'fabricator'],
59	  consumes: ['blockTypes'],
60	  // ...
61	}
62	```
