184	
185	### Behavior
186	
187	#### Spider: RigTemplateRegistry class
188	
189	A new `RigTemplateRegistry` class is added to `spider.ts`, following the `BlockTypeRegistry` pattern but with Loom-style qualified naming, config override, and dependency-scoped validation.
190	
191	**State:**
192	- `templates: Map<string, RigTemplate>` — merged template registry (config + kit-contributed, keyed by name)
193	- `configMappings: Map<string, string>` — config writ-type-to-template-name mappings
194	- `kitMappings: Map<string, string>` — kit-contributed mappings (first-registered wins)
195	- `designSourceMap: Map<string, string>` — engine designId → pluginId, built once at initialization
196	
197	**Registration (`registerFromKit(pluginId, kit, config)`):**
198	
199	When processing a kit's `rigTemplates` field:
200	1. Verify `rigTemplates` is a non-null object. If not, `console.warn` per R17 and skip.
201	2. For each `[templateName, template]` entry:
202	   - Compute qualified name: `${pluginId}.${templateName}`
203	   - If `config.rigTemplates` has a key matching the qualified name, skip silently (R2).
204	   - Validate the template shape: must have an `engines` array. If not, warn and skip (R17).
205	   - Run all template validation checks (R3, R9 of existing validation): non-empty engines, duplicate engine IDs, upstream refs, cycles, resolutionEngine, variable refs.
206	   - Run dependency-scoped designId check (R3): compute `allowedPlugins = new Set([pluginId, ...(kit.requires ?? []), ...(kit.recommends ?? []), 'spider'])`. For each engine, check `designSourceMap.get(engine.designId)` is in `allowedPlugins`, OR `engine.designId` is a Spider built-in engine ID.
207	   - If any check fails, `console.warn` with format per R18 and skip the entire template (R4).
208	   - If all checks pass, add to `templates` map under the qualified name.
209	
210	When processing a kit's `rigTemplateMappings` field:
211	1. Verify `rigTemplateMappings` is a non-null object. If not, warn and skip.
212	2. For each `[writType, templateName]` entry:
213	   - If `configMappings` has the same `writType` key, skip silently (R8).
214	   - If `kitMappings` already has the same `writType` key (from an earlier kit), `console.warn` about the duplicate (R8) and skip.
215	   - Otherwise, add to `kitMappings`.
216	3. Dangling reference validation is deferred (R12).
217	
218	**The designSourceMap** is built once at the beginning of `start()`:
219	1. Spider's built-in engine IDs (`draft`, `implement`, `review`, `revise`, `seal`) map to `'spider'`.
220	2. Scan `g.kits()`: for each kit with an `engines` field, iterate entries. For each value that has `id: string` and `run: function`, map `value.id → kit.id`.
221	3. Scan `g.apparatuses()`: for each apparatus with `supportKit.engines`, same logic, map `value.id → apparatus.id`.
222	
223	**`lookupTemplate(writType)` — uses closure state per D22:**
224	
225	```
226	function lookupTemplate(writType: string): RigTemplate {
227	  // Step 1: Config mapping for this writ type
228	  const configMapped = configMappings.get(writType);
229	  if (configMapped !== undefined) {
230	    const t = templateRegistry.get(configMapped);
231	    if (t) return t;
232	    // Config points to nonexistent template — validated at startup, should not happen at runtime
233	  }
234	
235	  // Step 2: Kit mapping for this writ type
236	  const kitMapped = kitMappings.get(writType);
237	  if (kitMapped !== undefined) {
238	    const t = templateRegistry.get(kitMapped);
239	    if (t) return t;
240	  }
241	
242	  // Step 1 (default): Config mapping for 'default'
243	  const configDefault = configMappings.get('default');
244	  if (configDefault !== undefined) {
245	    const t = templateRegistry.get(configDefault);
246	    if (t) return t;
247	  }
248	
249	  // Step 2 (default): Kit mapping for 'default'
250	  const kitDefault = kitMappings.get('default');
251	  if (kitDefault !== undefined) {
252	    const t = templateRegistry.get(kitDefault);
253	    if (t) return t;
254	  }
255	
256	  // Step 3: Template named 'default' in merged registry
257	  const defaultTemplate = templateRegistry.get('default');
258	  if (defaultTemplate) return defaultTemplate;
259	
260	  // Step 4: Throw
261	  throw new Error(
262	    `[spider] No rig template found for writ type "${writType}" and no "default" template or mapping configured.`
263	  );
264	}
265	```
266	
267	Note on lookup chain: the 'default' key in config/kit mappings is checked as part of steps 1-2 (as a special case of the mapping lookup), before the direct 'default' template lookup in step 3. This means `rigTemplateMappings: { "default": "quality-tools.audit" }` correctly routes unmatched writ types to the named kit template.
268	
269	**Deferred mapping validation (end of Phase 1, before Phase 2 subscription starts):**
270	
271	After all Phase 1a and 1b scanning is done:
272	1. For each entry in `configMappings`: if the template name is not in `templateRegistry`, throw (R12, R24).
273	2. For each entry in `kitMappings`: if the template name is not in `templateRegistry`, `console.warn` and remove the entry from `kitMappings` (R12, R24).
274	
275	**Phase 2 (plugin:initialized) incremental registration:**
276	
277	When a late-arriving apparatus supportKit is registered:
278	1. Process its `rigTemplates` normally (validate, register qualified names).
279	2. Process its `rigTemplateMappings` normally — for dangling references, validate immediately against the current `templateRegistry` state. If dangling, warn and skip (since the deferred pass already ran).
280	
281	#### Spider: `start()` changes
282	
283	The new `start()` flow:
284	
285	```
286	start(ctx: StartupContext): void {
287	  const g = guild();
288	  spiderConfig = g.guildConfig().spider ?? {};
289	  // ... existing apparatus lookups ...
290	
291	  // 1. Build designId → pluginId map
292	  buildDesignSourceMap(g.kits(), g.apparatuses());
293	
294	  // 2. Register config templates into templateRegistry
295	  //    (validate with existing validateTemplates — throws on error)
296	  if (spiderConfig.rigTemplates) {
297	    validateTemplates(spiderConfig.rigTemplates, fabricator);
298	    for (const [name, template] of Object.entries(spiderConfig.rigTemplates)) {
299	      templateRegistry.set(name, template);
300	    }
301	  }
302	
303	  // 3. Register config mappings into configMappings
304	  if (spiderConfig.rigTemplateMappings) {
305	    for (const [writType, templateName] of Object.entries(spiderConfig.rigTemplateMappings)) {
306	      configMappings.set(writType, templateName);
307	    }
308	  }
309	
310	  // 4. Phase 1a: Scan standalone kits
311	  for (const kit of g.kits()) {
312	    rigTemplateRegistry.registerFromKit(kit.id, kit.kit, spiderConfig);
313	  }
314	
315	  // 5. Phase 1b: Scan already-started apparatus supportKits
316	  for (const app of g.apparatuses()) {
317	    if (app.apparatus.supportKit) {
318	      rigTemplateRegistry.registerFromKit(app.id, app.apparatus.supportKit, spiderConfig);
319	    }
320	  }
321	
322	  // 6. Deferred mapping validation
323	  validateMappings();
324	
325	  // 7. Phase 2: Subscribe for late-arriving apparatus
326	  ctx.on('plugin:initialized', (plugin: unknown) => {
327	    const loaded = plugin as LoadedPlugin;
328	    if (isLoadedApparatus(loaded) && loaded.apparatus.supportKit) {
329	      rigTemplateRegistry.registerFromKit(loaded.id, loaded.apparatus.supportKit, spiderConfig);
330	      // Validate this kit's mappings immediately
331	      validateIncrementalMappings(loaded.id);
332	    }
333	    // Also register block types (existing behavior)
334	    if (isLoadedApparatus(loaded)) {
335	      blockTypeRegistry.register(loaded);
336	    }
337	  });
338	
339	  // ... existing book setup, kit block type scan, CDC handler ...
340	}
341	```
342	
343	The apparatus declaration changes to:
344	
345	```typescript
346	apparatus: {
347	  requires: ['stacks', 'clerk', 'fabricator'],
348	  consumes: ['blockTypes', 'rigTemplates', 'rigTemplateMappings'],
349	  // ...
350	}
351	```
352	
353	#### Clerk: writ type kit consumption
354	
355	**New inline state** in `createClerk()` closure:
356	
357	```typescript
358	/** Merged set of valid writ type names: builtins + config + kit contributions. */
359	let mergedWritTypes: Set<string>;
360	
361	/** Config-declared writ type names, for override checking during kit registration. */
362	let configWritTypeNames: Set<string>;
363	```
364	
365	**New registration function:**
366	
367	```typescript
368	function registerKitWritTypes(pluginId: string, kit: Record<string, unknown>): void {
369	  const raw = kit.writTypes;
370	  if (!Array.isArray(raw)) return;
371	
372	  for (const entry of raw) {
373	    if (typeof entry !== 'object' || entry === null || typeof (entry as Record<string, unknown>).name !== 'string') {
374	      console.warn(`[clerk] Kit "${pluginId}" writTypes: entry is missing required "name" field — skipped`);
375	      continue;
376	    }
377	    const name = (entry as WritTypeEntry).name;
378	
379	    // Config override: skip silently
380	    if (configWritTypeNames.has(name)) continue;
381	
382	    // Duplicate kit contribution: warn
383	    if (mergedWritTypes.has(name)) {
384	      console.warn(`[clerk] Kit "${pluginId}" writTypes: type "${name}" already registered by another kit — skipped`);
385	      continue;
386	    }
387	
388	    mergedWritTypes.add(name);
389	  }
390	}
391	```
392	
393	**`resolveWritTypes()` changes:**
394	
395	```typescript
396	function resolveWritTypes(): Set<string> {
397	  return mergedWritTypes;
398	}
399	```
400	
401	This function is now a simple getter — the set was populated at startup and updated by `plugin:initialized`.
402	
403	**`start()` changes:**
404	
405	```typescript
406	start(ctx: StartupContext): void {
407	  const g = guild();
408	  const stacks = g.apparatus<StacksApi>('stacks');
409	  writs = stacks.book<WritDoc>('clerk', 'writs');
410	  links = stacks.book<WritLinkDoc>('clerk', 'links');
411	
412	  // Initialize merged writ types from builtins + config
413	  const config = resolveClerkConfig();
414	  configWritTypeNames = new Set((config.writTypes ?? []).map((e) => e.name));
415	  mergedWritTypes = new Set([...BUILTIN_TYPES, ...configWritTypeNames]);
416	
417	  // Phase 1a: Scan standalone kits
418	  for (const kit of g.kits()) {
419	    registerKitWritTypes(kit.id, kit.kit);
420	  }
421	
422	  // Phase 1b: Scan already-started apparatus supportKits
423	  for (const app of g.apparatuses()) {
424	    if (app.apparatus.supportKit) {
425	      registerKitWritTypes(app.id, app.apparatus.supportKit);
426	    }
427	  }
428	
429	  // Phase 2: Subscribe for late-arriving apparatus supportKits
430	  ctx.on('plugin:initialized', (plugin: unknown) => {
431	    const loaded = plugin as LoadedPlugin;
432	    if (isLoadedApparatus(loaded) && loaded.apparatus.supportKit) {
433	      registerKitWritTypes(loaded.id, loaded.apparatus.supportKit);
434	    }
435	  });
436	},
437	```
438	
439	The apparatus declaration changes to:
440	
441	```typescript
442	apparatus: {
443	  requires: ['stacks'],
444	  consumes: ['writTypes'],
445	  // ...
446	}
447	```
448	
449	Note: the `start` parameter changes from `_ctx: StartupContext` to `ctx: StartupContext`.
450	
451	### Non-obvious Touchpoints
452	
453	- **`packages/plugins/spider/src/index.ts`** — must re-export `SpiderKit` from `./spider.ts`. The `SpiderConfig` type is already re-exported from `./types.ts`; the new `rigTemplateMappings` field on `SpiderConfig` is automatically included.
454	- **`packages/plugins/clerk/src/index.ts`** — must re-export `ClerkKit` from `./clerk.ts`.
455	- **`packages/plugins/spider/src/types.ts`** — the `GuildConfig` augmentation at the bottom already declares `spider?: SpiderConfig`. Since `SpiderConfig` gains `rigTemplateMappings`, the augmentation covers it automatically.
456	- **`packages/plugins/clerk/src/types.ts`** — the `GuildConfig` augmentation already declares `clerk?: ClerkConfig`. No changes needed.
457	- **Spider's existing blockType `plugin:initialized` handler** — currently only handles `isLoadedApparatus`. The new handler for rig templates also only fires for `isLoadedApparatus` (since kits are scanned in Phase 1a). These two subscriptions can be combined into a single `plugin:initialized` handler that does both block type and rig template registration.
458	- **`packages/plugins/spider/src/spider.test.ts`** — the `buildFixture()` function's `fakeGuild` object currently returns empty arrays from `kits()` and `apparatuses()`. Tests that exercise kit contributions need to extend `buildFixture()` to accept `LoadedKit[]` and return them from `kits()`.
459	- **`packages/plugins/clerk/src/clerk.test.ts`** — similarly, `fakeGuild.kits()` returns `[]` and `fakeGuild.apparatuses()` returns `[]`. Tests need to inject mock kits.
460	
461	## Validation Checklist
462	
463	- V1 [R1, R2]: Create a test where a kit contributes `rigTemplates: { audit: { engines: [...] } }` with pluginId `quality-tools`. Verify the template is registered under `quality-tools.audit`. Add a config template with the same qualified name and verify the kit contribution is skipped.
464	- V2 [R3, R4]: Create a test where a kit template references a designId from a plugin NOT in its `requires`/`recommends`. Verify a `console.warn` is emitted containing the kit name and the template is not registered. Then test with a designId from a declared dependency — verify it passes.
465	- V3 [R5, R6]: Create a test where a kit contributes `writTypes: [{ name: 'quality-audit' }]`. Post a writ with `type: 'quality-audit'` and verify it succeeds. Then add a config writType with the same name and verify the kit contribution is skipped. Then have two kits contribute the same name and verify a warning is logged.
466	- V4 [R7, R8]: Create a test where a kit contributes `rigTemplateMappings: { 'quality-audit': 'quality-tools.audit' }`. Verify that spawning a rig for a `quality-audit` writ uses the `quality-tools.audit` template. Then add a config mapping for the same writ type and verify the config mapping wins.
467	- V5 [R9, R10, R11]: Create a test with config `rigTemplates: { standard: {...} }, rigTemplateMappings: { mandate: 'standard', default: 'standard' }`. Post a mandate writ and verify it spawns using the `standard` template. Post an unknown-type writ and verify it falls back to `standard` via the `default` mapping.
468	- V6 [R9]: Create a test with NO mappings and a template named `default`. Verify that a writ of any type uses the `default` template (step 3 of lookup chain).
469	- V7 [R12]: Create a test where a kit mapping references a nonexistent template name. Verify a `console.warn` is emitted and the mapping is removed. Create a config mapping referencing a nonexistent template — verify startup throws.
470	- V8 [R13]: Verify Spider's apparatus declaration includes `consumes: ['blockTypes', 'rigTemplates', 'rigTemplateMappings']`.
471	- V9 [R14]: Verify Clerk's apparatus declaration includes `consumes: ['writTypes']`.
472	- V10 [R15]: Create a test where an apparatus supportKit contributes `rigTemplates` and verify Phase 1b scanning picks it up. Create a test where a late-arriving apparatus fires `plugin:initialized` with a supportKit containing `rigTemplateMappings` and verify Phase 2 registration works.
473	- V11 [R16]: Verify `SpiderKit` is exported from `@shardworks/spider-apparatus` and `ClerkKit` is exported from `@shardworks/clerk-apparatus`.
474	- V12 [R17, R18]: Create a test where a kit's `rigTemplates` field is a non-object (e.g., a number). Verify a `console.warn` is emitted with the kit name. Create a test where a kit template is missing the `engines` array. Verify a warning with the format `[spider] Kit "pluginId" rigTemplates.templateName: ...`.
475	- V13 [R19]: Verify that `resolveWritTypes()` returns the merged set including kit contributions, and that posting a writ with a kit-contributed type succeeds without re-reading config.
476	
477	## Test Cases
478	
479	### Spider — kit-contributed templates
480	
481	1. **Happy path: kit template registered under qualified name.** Kit `quality-tools` contributes `rigTemplates: { audit: { engines: [{ id: 'step1', designId: 'draft' }] } }`. After startup, spawning a writ with a mapping to `quality-tools.audit` uses that template. Verify rig has 1 engine with id `step1`.
482	
483	2. **Config override: qualified name in config skips kit.** Config has `rigTemplates: { 'quality-tools.audit': { engines: [...different...] } }`. Kit `quality-tools` also contributes `audit`. Verify the config template is used, not the kit's.
484	
485	3. **Dependency-scoped validation: allowed designId passes.** Kit with `requires: ['fabricator']` contributes a template referencing a designId contributed by the fabricator kit. Verify it registers.
486	
487	4. **Dependency-scoped validation: disallowed designId is rejected.** Kit with `requires: ['spider']` (no fabricator) contributes a template referencing a designId from fabricator. Verify console.warn and template not registered.
488	
489	5. **Dependency-scoped validation: kit's own engines are allowed.** Kit contributes both `engines: { custom: customEngine }` and `rigTemplates: { pipeline: { engines: [{ id: 'c', designId: 'custom' }] } }`. Verify template registers successfully.
490	
491	6. **Built-in Spider engines are always allowed.** Kit with empty `requires` contributes a template referencing `'draft'` (Spider built-in). Verify it registers.
492	
493	7. **Malformed kit template: missing engines array.** Kit contributes `rigTemplates: { bad: { notEngines: [] } }`. Verify console.warn and template not registered.
494	
495	8. **Malformed kit field: rigTemplates is not an object.** Kit contributes `rigTemplates: 'invalid'`. Verify console.warn, no crash.
496	
497	### Spider — kit-contributed mappings
498	
499	9. **Happy path: kit mapping routes writ type to template.** Kit contributes `rigTemplateMappings: { 'quality-audit': 'quality-tools.audit' }` and `rigTemplates: { audit: {...} }`. Spawn a `quality-audit` writ. Verify the `quality-tools.audit` template is used.
500	
501	10. **Config mapping overrides kit mapping.** Config has `rigTemplateMappings: { 'quality-audit': 'standard' }`. Kit also maps `quality-audit`. Verify config mapping wins.
502	
503	11. **Two kits map same writ type: first wins with warning.** Kit A and kit B both map `quality-audit`. Verify first-registered wins and console.warn is emitted.
504	
505	12. **Dangling mapping: kit mapping to nonexistent template.** Kit maps `quality-audit` to `nonexistent.template`. Verify console.warn after Phase 1 and mapping removed.
506	
507	13. **Dangling mapping: config mapping to nonexistent template.** Config maps `mandate` to `nonexistent`. Verify startup throws.
508	
509	14. **Cross-kit mapping reference.** Kit A contributes template `a.pipeline`. Kit B contributes mapping `{ 'task': 'a.pipeline' }` (B does NOT contribute the template). Verify the mapping resolves correctly.
510	
511	15. **Default mapping in config.** Config has `rigTemplateMappings: { 'default': 'quality-tools.audit' }`, kit contributes the template. Writ with an unmapped type. Verify it uses the `quality-tools.audit` template.
512	
513	16. **Default template fallback (no mappings at all).** Config has `rigTemplates: { 'default': {...} }`, no mappings. Writ with any type. Verify 'default' template is used.
514	
515	### Spider — lookup chain edge cases
516	
517	17. **No template, no mapping, no default.** Empty registries. Verify throw with descriptive error.
518	
519	18. **Config mapping takes precedence over kit mapping for same writ type.** Both define mappings for `mandate`. Verify config wins.
520	
521	### Clerk — kit-contributed writ types
522	
523	19. **Happy path: kit writ type allows posting.** Kit contributes `writTypes: [{ name: 'quality-audit' }]`. Post a writ with `type: 'quality-audit'`. Verify success.
524	
525	20. **Config override: config writType with same name skips kit.** Config has `writTypes: [{ name: 'quality-audit' }]`. Kit also contributes `quality-audit`. Verify no warning (silent skip).
526	
527	21. **Duplicate kit contributions: warning emitted.** Two kits contribute `writTypes: [{ name: 'quality-audit' }]`. Verify first wins, console.warn emitted.
528	
529	22. **Kit writ type does not affect built-in types.** Kit contributes `writTypes: [{ name: 'mandate' }]`. Verify `mandate` still works (it's built-in, so the kit contribution is redundant but harmless).
530	
531	23. **Unknown type still rejected.** No kit or config contributes `unknown-type`. Verify posting with that type throws.
532	
533	24. **Malformed kit writTypes entry.** Kit contributes `writTypes: [{ notName: 'bad' }]`. Verify console.warn and entry skipped.
534	
535	25. **Late-arriving apparatus supportKit writ type.** An apparatus fires `plugin:initialized` after Clerk starts, with `supportKit: { writTypes: [{ name: 'late-type' }] }`. Verify `late-type` is valid for posting.
536	
